  "texts": [
    "The ASCO core idea is to use scSE with asymmetric convolution (Fig. 7).The scSE component acts on the spatial and channel axes of the input feature maps, generating two activation Fig.",
    "5 The scSE structure maps, and then multiplies these with the input feature map to recalibrate the features.",
    "This adaptive adjustment allows the proposed ASD-Net network to obtain richer spatial and channel information at the pixel level.In addition, the ASCO block uses asymmetric convolution (vertical and horizontal) to better integrate spatial and channel information and deeply mine the correlation between features.",
    "For this, ASCO integrates complex asymmetric convolution operations and attention gates into a standard convolution operation.",
    "This design helps reduce computational complexity in practical applications and improve network runtime efficiency.The design of the ASCO block is well-grounded theoretically."
  ]
}